item.title: ASX finishes lower, healthcare among falls
item.description: The Australian share market opened in positive territory but gave up the gains to close marginally lower.

item.title: Hotel night guard ‘worked at Coles in day’
item.description: A security supervisor from one of Melbourne’s quarantine hotels has revealed one guard was working shifts at Coles before a 12-hour shift at the hotel.

item.title: Ingham’s profit plunges as virus dents demand
item.description: Ingham’s produced more poultry during the 2019-20 financial year but was hit by a fall in demand, while COVID-19 restrictions constrained supply chains and operations in Australia and New Zealand.

item.title: Bennett: Young is the man for Dragons top job
item.description: Wayne Bennett has backed Dean Young to be St George Illawarra’s next coach, declaring he possesses the qualities to be successful.

item.title: Four accused of prison murder
item.description: Four men have fronted court charged with a murder at a Melbourne prison.

item.title: Families ‘sleepless’ for 25 nights
item.description: Families living next to a 24-hour construction site in Melbourne’s north say the constant noise is such a disturbance the State Government is giving them exemption notices to travel outside 5km for “temporary relocation”.

item.title: Plea to WA, Tas: Open up your borders
item.description: The South Australian premier is calling for Tasmania and Western Australia to open their borders to the state, saying SA residents posed no threat.

item.title: $3m cold call scam hits 95-year-old
item.description: Two Brisbane-based international students have been arrested for their role in an international money laundering syndicate that duped hundreds of Australians out of a total of $3 million.

item.title: $500k reward for 24yo cold case
item.description: For almost 24 years, the Thurlow family have been left wondering what happened to Gregory James.

item.title: Couple breach border in freight truck
item.description: A Sydney couple has been fined more than $9000 after allegedly sneaking across the Queensland border in a freight truck.
